{"index": 184, "title": "Software Engineer", "job_location": "Cardiff, Wales, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "About UsAdam Health is redefining men\u2019s health, longevity and wellness tackling the problem that 1 in 5 men die prematurely from preventable conditions.\u00a0We do this with innovative, user-centered solutions that empower men to take proactive control of their health. This includes IP protected wearable technology, a partner app, a supplement and more coming. With early traction, a successful seed round, and a bold mission to lead an industry shift, we\u2019re on track to becoming a defining player in the men\u2019s health and wellness space.Position SummaryWe are hiring our second in-house Software Engineer moving away from having used an app agency.\u00a0This is a hands-on technical role.\u00a0The successful candidate will be responsible to help develop and maintain our native app, and a backend system for analysing and processing results. You will be supported by a lead engineer but we want to give someone the opportunity to grow and take responsibility.\u00a0This is not managing legacy fixed infrastructure.\u00a0This is a chance to help choose and shape the engineering set up as the company grows with high value proprietary data, AI and cutting edge technologies.\u00a0Why Join Us Now?As the second in-house engineering hire, you will be joining at a pivotal moment just as we close our second funding round. This is an opportunity for the right person that's looking for a hands on role with scope to grow. You will have the unique opportunity to shape our technical foundations and establish best practices before the base code becomes more complex.Experience we\u2019re looking for5+ years professional software engineering experience.Hands-on experience with mobile app development (production-level exposure).Experience with one or more of:React NativeFlutterSwiftKotlin / Java (Android)Experience of Python or Node.JS, ideally both.Backend & Systems KnowledgeUnderstanding of backend systems and API design.Object-oriented programming experience.Experience working with relational databases (e.g. RDS / PostgreSQL / MySQL).Understanding of microservice architectures and distributed systems.Experience with Node.js and/or Python in production environments.DesirableExperience maintaining and shipping mobile apps in App Store / Play Store.Exposure to cross-platform migrations (native \u2192 Flutter / React Native).Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines and cloud environments.Security-aware mindset, particularly around handling sensitive user data.Profile We\u2019re Looking ForComfortable working across the stack when required.Mobile Development experienceStartup culture experienceHappy operating under technical leadership and structured review.Pragmatic and delivery-focused.Strong communicator in a small team environment.Remote role but travel to Cardiff or Bristol every 2 weeks expected. Weekly during onboarding.\u00a0Why not to apply:We know how much effort can go into applying for a role and we don\u2019t want you to waste time if you don\u2019t have to. These are reasons not to apply.You are based overseas. This is a role for UK residents only.\u00a0You are not comfortable with ambiguity. There is always lots going on in start ups, you can\u2019t do everything so it\u2019s about being comfortable focusing on what is important to achieve the next goal.\u00a0You like focussing on a niche.\u00a0This is a role where you will have oversight or be doing a number of different things.\u00a0Career Growth & ImpactThis role is designed to evolve as the company and team expand. Although it is a mid level role we want to empower and support the person and give them the chance to grow. You will be instrumental in building the future engineering department at Adam Health.Work Environment & LogisticsLocation: This is a remote position for residents of the UK. No sponsorship is available.You will be required to commute to Cardiff or Bristol weekly during onboarding then approx every 2 weeks, thereafter.\u00a0This is to work with the Engineering and Product leads and will be in a co-working space and location is flexible between Cardiff and Bristol.Compensation & BenefitsSalary: Determined by your level of experience but we estimate the range to be \u00a350-60k.\u00a0Equity: Share options package, allowing you to share directly in our success.Benefits: Pension scheme and a holiday allowance of 25 vacation days with more benefits in the process of being added as the business grows.Application ProcessTo apply, please submit your CV. A cover letter is optional but preferred to help us understand why you want to work for Adam Health, why this role and why now. It\u2019s ok to use AI to help, proficiency in AI is encouraged, but make sure it reflects your genuine voice and experience.\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "Cardiff, Wales, United Kingdom", "loc": "UK_OTHER", "arr_raw": "This is a remote position for residents of the UK. No sponsorship is available.\nYou will be required to commute to Cardiff or Bristol weekly during onboarding then approx every 2 weeks, thereafter.", "arr": "HYBRID", "sen_raw": "Software Engineer", "sen": "LEVEL_2", "tech_raw": "React NativeFlutterSwiftKotlin / Java (Android)Experience of Python or Node.JS, ideally both.Node.js and/or Python in production environments.AI", "tech": ["NODE", "REACT", "AI_ML"], "comp_raw": "Salary: Determined by your level of experience but we estimate the range to be \u00a350-60k.", "comp": "RANGE_45_54K"}}
{"index": 185, "title": "Senior Engineer", "job_location": "London Area, United Kingdom (Hybrid)", "jd_text": "About the job                                                               This is a job that Jill, our AI Recruiter, is recruiting for on behalf of one of our customers.She will pick the best candidates from Jack's network.The next step is to speak to Jack.Senior EngineerCompany Description: VC-backed fintech startupJob Description:You will join a high-growth fintech building next-generation financial infrastructure for emerging markets. As an early engineering hire, you will design and scale robust systems that bridge traditional finance with modern digital rails. This role offers the opportunity to lead complex technical projects while directly impacting global trade efficiency and financial inclusion.Location: London, UKWhy this role is remarkable:      Opportunity to build core infrastructure at the intersection of traditional finance and digital assets for high-impact markets.Join a well-funded team backed by top-tier VCs at an early, high-leverage stage where you can shape technical direction.Work in a fast-paced environment that prioritizes technical excellence, autonomy, and the use of cutting-edge AI-driven developer tools. What you will do:      Design, develop, and maintain large-scale payment infrastructure and backend systems to handle complex global transactions.Build and optimize internal AI infrastructure and tooling to enhance developer experience and operational efficiency.Collaborate across the stack to integrate diverse financial systems, treasury functions, and modern distributed ledger technologies. The ideal candidate:      Significant experience in full-stack engineering with a focus on high-performance backend systems, payments, or trading infrastructure.Ambitious and autonomous professional who thrives in high-growth environments and has experience wearing multiple hats.Strong technical foundation in relational databases, distributed systems, and a deep interest in leveraging AI and blockchain technology. Who are Jack & Jill?Ok, I'll go first. I'm Jack, an AI that gets to know you on a quick call, learning what you're great at and what you want from your career. Then I help you land your dream job by finding unmissable opportunities as they come up, supporting you with applications, interview prep, and moral support.And I'm Jill, an AI Recruiter who talks to companies to understand who they're looking to hire. Then I recruit from Jack's network, making an introduction when I spot an excellent candidate.Next stepsStep 1. Visit our website.Step 2. Click 'Talk to Jack'.Step 3. Talk to Jack so he can understand your experience and ambitions.Step 4. Jack will make sure Jill (the AI agent working for the company) considers you for this role.Step 5. If Jill thinks you're a great fit and her client wants to meet you, they will make the introduction.Step 6. If not, Jack will find you excellent alternatives. All for free.We never post fake jobsThis isn't a trick. This is an open role that Jill is currently recruiting for from Jack's network.Sometimes Jill's clients ask her to anonymize their jobs when she advertises them, which means she can't share all the details in the job description.We appreciate this can make them look a bit suspect, but there isn't much we can do about it.Give Jack a spin! You could land this role. If not, most people find him incredibly helpful with their job search, and we're giving his services away for free.                                                                                                                              See more\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "London Area, United Kingdom (Hybrid)", "loc": "IN_LONDON", "arr_raw": "Hybrid", "arr": "HYBRID", "sen_raw": "Senior Engineer", "sen": "LEVEL_3", "tech_raw": "AI, blockchain technology", "tech": ["AI_ML"], "comp_raw": null, "comp": "NO_GBP"}}
