{"index": 233, "title": "Mid-level Software Engineer", "job_location": "London Area, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "\ud83d\ude80 We\u2019re hiring a Mid-level Full Stack Engineer at Birl \ud83d\ude80At Birl, we\u2019re building the future of returns for e-commerce. Our mission is simple: make returns effortless for shoppers, valuable for brands, and better for the planet.We\u2019re a small, ambitious startup tackling a problem that touches millions of online purchases every day. There\u2019s a lot to build, plenty of unknowns, and huge opportunity ahead. If you enjoy ownership, moving fast, and figuring things out as you go, you\u2019ll feel very at home here.Now is a brilliant time to join as we scale our platform, deepen our integrations, and work towards becoming the go-to global returns solution \ud83c\udf0d\u267b\ufe0fThe roleWe\u2019re looking for a Mid-level/weight Full Stack Software Engineer to join our small engineering team. You\u2019ll work collaboratively in the tech team and the wider team to build and evolve Birl\u2019s core product, from customer-facing returns flows to merchant dashboards and backend services.This is a hands-on role with real ownership. You\u2019ll help shape technical decisions, influence how we build, and ship things that customers actually use.What you\u2019ll be doing:Designing, building and shipping features across the full stack, from user interfaces through to backend services and data layers.Developing and maintaining scalable backend services and APIs in Node.js, with a strong focus on reliability, performance and security.Contributing to high-quality customer and merchant experiences using React and Next.js.Building and maintaining integrations with e-commerce platforms, particularly Shopify.Working with GCP to deploy, monitor and scale systems in a production environment.Taking ownership of features from early discovery and technical design through to launch, monitoring and iteration.Contributing to sensible engineering practices, documentation and code quality as the team and codebase grow.What we\u2019re looking for:Strong commercial experience working full stack with JavaScript, including React or Next.js and Node.js.A genuine interest in backend engineering, with solid experience building APIs, integrations and production systems.Experience working in e-commerce, including platform integrations such as Shopify.Good technical judgement and the ability to make pragmatic decisions within an evolving architecture.Comfortable working in a small, fast-moving team with ambiguity and changing priorities.A proactive, delivery-focused mindset balanced with care for quality, testing and maintainability.Someone who enjoys ownership and takes pride in seeing features through from idea to production.Startup experience is a plus, but not essential if you thrive in fast-paced environments.Why Birl?High impact role with genuine ownership from day one.Small team, no layers, and lots of influence.Meaningful work at the intersection of e-commerce and sustainability.Big ambition, fast learning, and plenty of room to grow with the company.Stages:Drop us an email with your CV at hello@wearebirl.com with the subject: \"Birl \ud83d\udfe3\" to show you've at least read this part of the job descriptionInitial 15 min chat with a member of our teamA 30-60 min session with one of our engineersMeet one (or both) of our foundersWe aim to get back to you within a few days no matter which stage you're at - to the best of our ability anyway! If you\u2019re excited by early-stage energy, enjoy solving real problems, and want to help shape a product and team from the inside - we\u2019d love to hear from you! Compensation: \u00a350-70k (depending on experience)Location: Hybrid (London-based) Disclaimer: We're currently not working with any recruiters.\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "London Area, United Kingdom", "loc": "IN_LONDON", "arr_raw": "Hybrid (London-based)", "arr": "HYBRID", "sen_