{"index": 241, "title": "Graduate Software Engineer", "job_location": "Germany", "jd_text": "About The TeamAs engineers at Miro, we build a product that allows users to create the next big thing and we try to do this by shipping value to customers ever faster, at high quality. Our vision is collective, never independent: We\u2019re a part of a greater organization, supporting the Miro and Product Engineering visions and the ways our customers work in this new hybrid space.We\u2019re working on something new and complex, and developing it fast. We\u2019ve scaled quickly to 60M users, so staying relevant for our customers means releasing new features while keeping our core product running smoothly. Miro\u2019s user base is as diverse as it is global in reach. Curiosity combined with a commitment to build highly functional software enables us to make a positive impact for our users, whether they\u2019re small businesses or entire governments.Our Engineering Team consists of 700 engineers located in several hubs and divided across several areas like Product development, infrastructure, data engineering and machine learning.About The ProgramThe Miro Software Engineering Graduate Programme is designed to help computer science graduates launch their careers. In our 12-month programme, you'll gain hands-on experience working on real-world projects. You'll also be mentored by expert software engineers, who will help you develop your skills and career.We understand that at this stage of your career you might not be sure yet where you want to specialize and what roles you will find the most enjoyable. What we do know is that building something that people love is exciting and why we are here.We will give you a broad experience, from working on a product development team building features millions of users will love to experiencing how we use data to make this happen.You will spend time working with engineers, product managers, designers, analytics, ux researchers to look at a 